80 int32_t DPU_StaticClutterProc_configEdma(DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj *obj)

94

100  syncABCfg.srcBIdx = numRxTimesNumRange * sampleLenInBytes;
101  syncABCfg.dstBIdx = sampleLenInBytes;
102  syncABCfg.srcCIdx = 2 * sampleLenInBytes;//2 factor due to ping/pong

110  true,//isIntermediateTransferCompletionEnabled
111  true,//isTransferCompletionEnabled

113  NULL);//transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg

215 int32_t DPU_StaticClutterProc_waitInData(DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj *obj, uint32_t pingPongId)
216 {
217  /* wait until transfer done */
218  volatile bool isTransferDone;
219  uint8_t chId;
220  int32_t retVal = 0;
221 
222  if(pingPongId == DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_PING_IDX)
223  {
224  chId = obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.ping.channel;
225  }
226  else
227  {
228  chId = obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.pong.channel;
229  }
230  do
231  {
232  retVal = EDMA_isTransferComplete(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle,
233  chId,
234  (bool *)&isTransferDone);
235  if(retVal != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
236  {
237  return retVal;
238  }
239  } while (isTransferDone == false);
240 
241  return 0;
242 }

289 #ifdef SUBSYS_DSS
290 #include <ti/alg/mmwavelib/mmwavelib.h>
303 static inline void DPU_StaticClutterProc_clutterRemoval(DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj *obj, cmplx16ImRe_t *inputBuf)
304 {
305  uint32_t sumVal[2]={0};
306  cmplx32ImRe_t *pSumVal = (cmplx32ImRe_t *) sumVal;
307  uint32_t meanVal;
308  cmplx16ImRe_t *pMeanVal = (cmplx16ImRe_t *) &meanVal;
309 
310  /* Assume that scratch buffer is not initialized. Even if it is initialized to zeros,
311  after every call of mmwavelib_vecsubc() below the full buffer will be updated (all samples).
312  Therefore, we need to pad the scratch buffer with zeros in the last X samples. X can
313  be 0,1,2,3. In fact, X = obj->sizePingBufSamples - obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps)
314  This should be done every time this API is called, for both ping and pong.
315  When this API is called inputBuf[] already has the contents of the radarCube transferred in,
316  therefore only the trully padded samples should be set to zero.
317  Also note that if numDopplerChirps is already a multiple of 4, then no padding should be done.
318  R4F does not use the padded samples so this is not necessary.*/
319  if(obj->sizePingBufSamples > obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps)
320  {
321  memset((void*)&inputBuf[obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps],
322  0,
323  (obj->sizePingBufSamples - obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps) * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t));
324  }
325 
326  /*Lib requires size to be multiple of 4*/
327  mmwavelib_vecsum((int16_t *) inputBuf,
328  (int32_t *) sumVal,
329  (int32_t) obj->sizePingBufSamples);
330 
331  /*Divide by numDopplerChirps as the scratch buffer was padded to zero to make it a
332  multiple of 4 so it does not affect the average*/
333  pMeanVal->real = pSumVal->real / obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps ;
334  pMeanVal->imag = pSumVal->imag / obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps ;
335 
336  /*Lib requires size to be multiple of 4*/
337  mmwavelib_vecsubc((int16_t *) inputBuf,
338  (int16_t *) inputBuf,
339  (uint32_t) meanVal,
340  (int32_t) obj->sizePingBufSamples);
341 }
342 #endif

357 static inline void DPU_StaticClutterProc_clutterRemoval(DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj *obj, cmplx16ImRe_t *inputBuf)
358 {
359  uint32_t dopIdx;
360  cmplx32ImRe_t sumVal;
361  cmplx16ImRe_t meanVal;
362  int32_t *a;
363  int32_t *b;
364 
365  sumVal.real = 0;
366  sumVal.imag = 0;
367 
368  for (dopIdx = 0; dopIdx < obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps; dopIdx++)
369  {
370  sumVal.real += inputBuf[dopIdx].real;
371  sumVal.imag += inputBuf[dopIdx].imag;
372  }
373 
374  meanVal.real = sumVal.real / obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps;
375  meanVal.imag = sumVal.imag / obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps;
376 
377  b = (int32_t*)&meanVal;
378  a = (int32_t*)&inputBuf[0];
379  for (dopIdx = 0; dopIdx < obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps; dopIdx++)
380  {
381  /*Implementing the following subtraction
382  inputBuf[dopIdx].real -= meanVal.real;
383  inputBuf[dopIdx].imag -= meanVal.imag;
384  using intrinsics below.
385  Note that the intrinsics below also
386  saturates instead of overflowing.
387  */
388  *a = _qsub16(*(a++),*b);
389  }
390 }
391 #endif

419 int32_t DPU_StaticClutterProc_process
420 (
421  DPU_StaticClutterProc_Handle handle,
422  DPU_StaticClutterProc_OutParams *outParams
423 )
424 {
425  DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj *obj;
426  int32_t retVal = 0;
427  uint32_t pingPongIdx = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_PING_IDX;
428  uint32_t nextPingPongIdx;
429  uint32_t idx, txAntIdx, firstSampleIdx;
430  cmplx16ImRe_t *radarCubeBase;
431  cmplx16ImRe_t *scratchBase;
432 
433  if(handle == NULL)
434  {
435  retVal = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_EINVAL;
436  goto exit;
437  }
438 
439  obj = (DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj*) handle;
440 
441  radarCubeBase = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)obj->cfg.hwRes.radarCube.data;
442  scratchBase = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)obj->cfg.hwRes.scratchBuf.buf;
443 
444  for(txAntIdx = 0; txAntIdx < obj->cfg.staticCfg.numTxAntennas; txAntIdx++)
445  {
446  /*Need to set correct EDMA source address for the first transfer
447  of every TX antenna.*/
448  firstSampleIdx = txAntIdx*obj->cfg.staticCfg.numRangeBins*obj->cfg.staticCfg.numRxAntennas*obj->cfg.staticCfg.numDopplerChirps;
449 
450  /* EDMA IN channels */
451  retVal = EDMA_setSourceAddress(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle,
452  obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.ping.channel,
453  (uint32_t)(SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)(&radarCubeBase[firstSampleIdx]),
454  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL)));
455  if(retVal < 0)
456  {
457  goto exit;
458  }
459 
460  retVal = EDMA_setSourceAddress(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle,
461  obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.pong.channel,
462  (uint32_t)(SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)(&radarCubeBase[firstSampleIdx + 1]),
463  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL)));
464 
465  if(retVal < 0)
466  {
467  goto exit;
468  }
469 
470  /* EDMA OUT channels */
471  retVal = EDMA_setDestinationAddress(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle,
472  obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaOut.ping.channel,
473  (uint32_t)(SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)(&radarCubeBase[firstSampleIdx]),
474  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL)));
475  if(retVal < 0)
476  {
477  goto exit;
478  }
479 
480  retVal = EDMA_setDestinationAddress(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle,
481  obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaOut.pong.channel,
482  (uint32_t)(SOC_translateAddress((uint32_t)(&radarCubeBase[firstSampleIdx + 1]),
483  SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL)));
484  if(retVal < 0)
485  {
486  goto exit;
487  }
488 
489  /* Always start with ping buffer */
490  pingPongIdx = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_PING_IDX;
491 
492  /* trigger first DMA */
493  retVal = EDMA_startDmaTransfer(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle, obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.ping.channel);
494  if(retVal < 0)
495  {
496  goto exit;
497  }
498 
499  for (idx = 0; idx < obj->cfg.staticCfg.numRangeBins*obj->cfg.staticCfg.numRxAntennas; idx++)
500  {
501  /* kick off next DMA */
502  if (idx < obj->cfg.staticCfg.numRangeBins * obj->cfg.staticCfg.numRxAntennas - 1)
503  {
504  nextPingPongIdx = pingPongIdx^1;
505 
506  /* Wait for the previous output transfer to finish for the ping/pong
507  buffer that will be triggered now to make sure scratch buffer can be overwritten
508  with new input data.*/
509  if(idx > 1)
510  {
511  retVal = DPU_StaticClutterProc_waitOutData (obj, nextPingPongIdx);
512  if(retVal < 0)
513  {
514  goto exit;
515  }
516  }
517 
518  if (nextPingPongIdx == DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_PONG_IDX)
519  {
520  retVal = EDMA_startDmaTransfer(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle, obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.pong.channel);
521  }
522  else
523  {
524  retVal = EDMA_startDmaTransfer(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle, obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaIn.ping.channel);
525  }
526  if(retVal < 0)
527  {
528  goto exit;
529  }
530  }
531 
532  /* verify that previous DMA has completed */
533  retVal = DPU_StaticClutterProc_waitInData (obj, pingPongIdx);
534  if(retVal < 0)
535  {
536  goto exit;
537  }
538 
539  /* Execute the clutter removal algorithm*/
540  DPU_StaticClutterProc_clutterRemoval(obj,
541  (cmplx16ImRe_t *)&scratchBase[pingPongIdx * obj->sizePingBufSamples]);
542 
543  /* Move data back to L3*/
544  if (pingPongIdx == DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_PONG_IDX)
545  {
546  retVal = EDMA_startDmaTransfer(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle, obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaOut.pong.channel);
547  }
548  else
549  {
550  retVal = EDMA_startDmaTransfer(obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaHandle, obj->cfg.hwRes.edmaOut.ping.channel);
551  }
552  if(retVal < 0)
553  {
554  goto exit;
555  }
556 
557  pingPongIdx ^= 1;
558  }
559  }
560 
561  /*Wait for last transfer to finish*/
562  /*Need to reset the index to the previous one that was sent out*/
563  pingPongIdx ^= 1;
564  retVal = DPU_StaticClutterProc_waitOutData (obj, pingPongIdx);
565  if(retVal < 0)
566  {
567  goto exit;
568  }
569 
570 exit:
571  return retVal;
572 }

574 int32_t DPU_StaticClutterProc_config
575 (
576  DPU_StaticClutterProc_Handle handle,
577  DPU_StaticClutterProc_Config *cfg
578 )
579 {
580  int32_t retVal = 0;
581  DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj *obj;
582 
583  /* Validate params */
584  if(!handle ||
585  !cfg ||
586  !cfg->hwRes.edmaHandle ||
587  !cfg->hwRes.radarCube.data ||
588  !cfg->hwRes.scratchBuf.buf ||
589  !cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps
590  )
591  {
592  retVal = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_EINVAL;
593  goto exit;
594  }
595 
596  obj = (DPU_StaticClutterProc_Obj*) handle;
597 
598  /* Check if radar cube format is supported by DPU*/
599  if(cfg->hwRes.radarCube.datafmt != DPIF_RADARCUBE_FORMAT_1)
600  {
601  retVal = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_EINVAL;
602  goto exit;
603  }
604 
605  #ifdef SUBSYS_DSS
606  /* Check if scratch buffer has correct alignment*/
607  if MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.scratchBuf.buf, DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_SCRATCHBUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT_DSP)
608  {
609  retVal = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_ESCRATCHBUF;
610  goto exit;
611  }
612 
613  /* The size of each scratch buffer (ping and pong - in samples) must be at minimum the
614  smallest multiple of 4 greater or equal to numDopplerChirps.*/
615  obj->sizePingBufSamples = ((cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps + 3) & ~0x0003);
616  #else
617  /* Check if scratch buffer has correct alignment*/
618  if MEM_IS_NOT_ALIGN(cfg->hwRes.scratchBuf.buf, DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_SCRATCHBUFFER_BYTE_ALIGNMENT_R4F)
619  {
620  retVal = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_ESCRATCHBUF;
621  goto exit;
622  }
623 
624  /* The size of each scratch buffer (ping and pong - in samples) must be at least as big as numDopplerChirps*/
625  obj->sizePingBufSamples = cfg->staticCfg.numDopplerChirps;
626  #endif
627 
628  /* Check if scratch buffer is big enough*/
629  if(cfg->hwRes.scratchBuf.bufSize < obj->sizePingBufSamples * 2 * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t))
630  {
631  retVal = DPU_STATICCLUTTERPROC_ESCRATCHBUF;
632  goto exit;
633  }
634 
635  /* Save config parameters */
636  memcpy((void *)&obj->cfg, (void *)cfg, sizeof(DPU_StaticClutterProc_Config));
637 
638  /* Configure EDMAs */
639  retVal = DPU_StaticClutterProc_configEdma(obj);
640  if(retVal < 0)
641  {
642  goto exit;
643  }
644 
645 exit:
646  return retVal;
647 }
